content: Good game but the app is clunky, confusing, and sometimes refuses to let you play online
The wall is too thin and very difficult to see especially on tiny phone screen. Appreciate if the developer could thicken the wall. Thanks

irritating!!!!! When playing online a box appears which blocks your view asking you to opt for lobby or new game. This is very annoying. It blocks your view of the tile values and is totally not needed. Not an enjoyable experience. Connection fails, screen freezes. Should ask for money back on app. You can never quit multiplayer games, it continues to ask you to finish them even though you may have aborted them many times..

The game itself is worthy of 5 stars (own the tablet board game too). The app could use some tweaks. The 3D look is a nice idea, but too cluttered for clear game play, end up using 2D most of the time. Had a few freezes that halted have play. But my biggest disappointment was the expansions. No matter how many you've purchased, you can only use a max of FOUR at a time. That should have been made clear. And it certainly isn't a prerequisite in the physical game.

My main problem with it is that the AI is extremely "lucky": multiple rounds in a row it can buy multiple cards in a row. The cards can get small and difficult to see. It doesn't appear that you can save a game, so you have to finish it in one go.
Cannot zoom in or out on the board. Also cannot create a new profile as it keeps telling me I have not entered a profile name despite having done so.
Great game. Okay digital version. Needs more expansions. I can't zoom in since the latest update.
How on earth do you set up an online game with friends?
Have only played the tutorial so far, but this seems like it will be a great game. Cannot wait to learn the strategies for winning gameplay. (All extensions purchased)
Ugly UI
So the online and multiplayer just doesn't work so I uninstalled the app as wasn't looking to play with bots. If you like to play with AI then go for it as the Graphics are good.

Can't save a profile because it says you must ever a name, even though a name is there. Freezes whenever attempting to register a profile for online play. Several spelling errors and just minor issues. Needs a lot of work.
Not functioning. Doesn't allow you to save a profile, saying you've not entered a name, regardless of what you've typed in the name field.
Love it.
Great implementation of a very fun game! I definitely recommend it

Tried to log in, didn't recognise my username/password no option to reset so I can wave "bye bye" to the extensions I paid for. Tried to register again and was continuously told that the online name I choose already exists even when I mashed the keyboard creating a string of random letters TWICE still, apparently, these strings of random letters have already been adopted as usernames. The game itself is good but my frustration at the loss of money and inept login/register procedure means 1 star.

Great game BUT please fix the following bug: EVERY TIME an online game continues on overnight it crashes and neither of us are able to make a move. Because of this I can't finish any of my games. Please fix this.

The app is functional, but definitely not efficient. There are a few bugs I've run into on a consistent basis. Restarting the app usually fixes, but if i were playing online it would be unbelievably frustrating. Oh, but there's no online population here. So maybe it works with friends in private matches?
I did not care for the game. The app works well on a Samsung. No problems or glitches.

The app: it's like an amateur open-source free game. Really bad 
programming, bugs everywhere. Really bad U.I. with buttons that obscure 
other buttons, the multiplayer setup is just mad and doesn't resemble 
anything you've ever seen before. The game: this game is so dry that I am 
now an actual mummy. Presumably the Iberian setting is some sort of 
subliminal trick to make you find this acceptable. I can't see any other 
connection to the theme. Basically, there are 2 decks of coloured tiles and 
you try to collect said colours better than the other person using the time 
honoured strategy of 'luck'. My partner and I got a few chuckles laughing 
at the expense of this game, but that's the most you can hope for.

A fun recreation of the board game that is unfortunately riddled with bugs and issues. I have encountered problems during multiple plays. Even with that said, the game is still fun when it works and provides a great experience with interesting graphics. The AI is also challenging to play against. DLC is available and although it is mostly $.99, there is a lot of it and I am uncomfortable buying something when the game has not been updated in so long. Highly recommended as long as you don't mind the rough edges.
Nearly unplayable implementation of one of my favorite tabletop games. Makes me sad.
Some issues. Online is unplayable as a "back to lobby" button covers the action selections. AI gets stuck if the money runs out. Looks like this wasn't QAed much if at all.
True to the board game... very fun.  The letters on the tiles are little small on your phone.  And there's a bug where it sometimes congratulates the wrong winner when playing vs AI. :)
I try to play online and Always says that there is no connection to server, I uninstalled and installed, I tried to go through WiFi and my cellphone internet and non worked. Any suggestions?

Game does not allow or at least does not explain how to quit the game when online. Keeps creating new games. Cannot play because it allows me only to go to the lobby or move to a new game. Irritating! Has to be fixed! The connection to server keeps dropping. NOT WORTH THE MONEY. FIX IT! The game itself is cool, i have it in cards' format and really enjoy it. This app is a disappointment.

Update..  just bought 5 expansions to this game, and none of them works. Can't even activate them.  It only shows that I have made purchases but doesn't do anything else. Pissed off. No instructions either.  ___________ I think this is a great game but they should improve on the online multi-player part. I started so many games to play online, but no one ever joins, except one, because no one (not even I) knows how to join or find an open game online. There is no instruction to tell you how. Also, I suggest they should add a chat screen to allow people playing online to communicate.

Playing against 5 hard AI.  Game freezes when the money runs out.  AI will not overpay for a tile (even though ALL the AI players have 10-20 money cards)and has no money cards to pick from....so it does nothing.  Have to abort game time after time.   Add on expansions are WAYYYYY overpriced.

Game keeps crashing. Starts, looks OK but first buy, first money pick and it closes with message saying "Unfortunately Alhambra has stopped" . Restart game, it offers to continue last game but proceeds to crash again. Uninstalled, reinstalled a few times but no go. Works fine on my phone though.
It's a great digital version of a fantastic game.

The gameplay is great. Unfortunately the app is a bit buggy. Sometimes it locks up and you have to 'abort' turn continue the game to get it working. The high scores and achievements plain don't work and selecting money can be fiddly. But it's playable and a great game. Shame the extensions are so pricey as I would have liked to try them.
Interface is unintuitive and confusing. Online player base is non-existent, probably due to the poor design.

Game works and plays very well. It is a bit tough to play on a phone screen. People who complain about not being able to rotate tiles are thinking carcassonne not alhambra,where you were never able to do that. Where are all of the great expansions? I would pay to play them
We need MORE boardgame apps!!  Please!
Good game but had trouble with rearranging my tiles. Would not allow me to move some tiles I should have been able to.
So got this for multi-player but can't create an account. Keeps saying name and password has to be 3-30 characters when it is.

The game plays single player fine, but it refuses to let me register for online play. No matter what combination I do, it just keeps telling me my online name and password must be between 3 and 30 characters (even when they both already are).
The game crashes nearly every time my family tries to play it.

Was working fine after buying it, but now it crashes every time I try to start a game. Multiplayer works, but you have to figure it out for yourself. The documentation for this doesn't seem to exist. Speaking as someone who owns the board game, I'm very disappointed in the Android version.
Seems like a good game, but it crashes Everytime it runs.

I hesitated before buying this due to the negative reviews, but glad I did as most of the complaints are unfounded. For example lots of people have said that it's hard to see and select your cards when you have lots of them but they are wrong, you simply hold your finger on them and they expand so its easy. I've had no trouble playing this and really enjoy it.
The numbers on the building cards are not clear. I enjoy the game but get tired of holding my device just so in order to see the cost of the building.

I don't know what I'm doing wrong and the game doesn't offer any assistance.  Selecting money is hard, and once I've managed to buy the building dragging it to the map accomplishes nothing, available spaces will not highlight and the building won't attach.  Very frustrating.
Excellent port

I enjoy the game but find the touch screen selecting really fussy when you're trying to select currency.  If you have a lot of cards it is almost impossible to select the correct cards to purchase items which is extremely frustrating.
The AI provides a good challenge. Very good UI. The developer continues to update even after the game has been out for quite awhile, which is unusual in a good way.
Decent port of a classic board game. AI is no slouch.

But I have to take another star off. I really this game but it's full of bugs. Every so often my screen goes black and my money disapears, making the frame unplayable, and it's the only game where my touchscreen seems weirdly unrrsponsive.

The worst thing about the previous version were the fact you need to be connected to download assets every. single. time. and the tricky card selection interface. However, this update has caused it to be unusable altogether. Each time I start a game it crashes without fail. It begins to load the play screen and closes. Very disappointing
I like the game, but not being able to save a game is a complete deal breaker for me. Fix it and I will play again (and perhaps purchase expansions!)

Please add this game to family library. Also for whatever reason you can only play this game when connected to WiFi (mobile network won't work), which doesn't make any sense when you play with a computer.
Please add to family library
First off, anyone saying that this game would be better if you could rotate tiles has obviously never played Alhambra. The interface could use updating.
Awesome game!  Looks boring but its a good game for the brain.

Alhambra is one of my favourite board games.  The app does a passable version of the game once you get used the the user interface.  Big issue is no save or resume on a game.  UX is hard to understand the first time you play. After you get it it works reasonably well.

The base game is fantastic, but I've found that the expansions have added less than I expected to the gameplay. The overall layout is very clear, though when you have more than 7 or 8 cards in hand they become difficult to see and select. Other than that, I have two complaints. First, the AI seems to freeze periodically when playing with the currency exchange extension. Second, there is no good way to consult the rules in the middle of a game. Oh, and a way to save games would be nice.

The overall game play mechanics are great, graphics are nice, but it crashes 99% of the time I try to play it.  This happened on my old phone and also on my new phone.  I've uninstalled/reinstalled twice with the same results.
Can't play. Keep getting a "Resources failed to download" error.

I can't move this app to my SD card. It's stuck on my phone, taking up a lot of the limited space on my phone. With all the apps and all the data that I want to install, there's not enough space on the phone. I need to be able to move it to the SD card.

Took me awhile to figure out how to do everything, and I've played the tabletop game. The layout is confusing, and the win/lose message plus "play again" is so tiny I didnt even see it at first and thought the game froze. All in all once you figure it out it is fun, but it really could use some help from a mobile user experience & design team.
Great to get reacquainted with this game. Where are the expansions though??

Took ages to figure out how to set up a profile as the register button was greyed out until a mystery tick was clicked, then it was impossible to create or see any online games after an initial 'connection to the network' was followed on the next screen with 'no network connection'. A truly awful implementation and completely unintuitive development of a game I love in real life. Dreadful.
Really bad

Tried to download this 3 times and it keeps crashing at 87%. Don't say it's my internet because I have a 60mb vdsl link and a 4g link at over 50mb n they both had the same issue. I rebooted my phn n tried again. Same issue. Samsung G5

Cumbersome UI. Totally unintuitive and no help from any type of tutorial that I can see. Couldn't register an account either. Needs work and without any of the expansions the game can be kind of boring.
Shame.

Got the game and tried to play it on a Note 4. Every tile and button were minute, had to use the stylus with some success. It was very frustrating, even though the game engine followed the rules to the letter. Playable, but with lots of swear words. But that was then. The layout of the new upgrade is way better. No need for a stylus. Well done devs.
I can play it again after the game has problem in previous version. I think the game is fun. it's easy to play but hard to win and it's can replayable, not boring and many bugs have fixed. I give 5*.
replyContent: We finally found the problem and solved it with the new version. Have fun again!

replyContent: We finally found the problem and solved it with the new version. Have fun again!

content: Good job guys all working now!
replyContent: We finally found the problem and solved it with the new version. Have fun again!

content: Wouldn't update so did a reinstall. Now it won't even open. Did originally ask if we would be seeing digital versions of the extensions but I guess priority is to have a stable base game before we invest in extras!
replyContent: We finally found the problem and solved it with the new version. Have fun again!

content: Please fix it
replyContent: We finally found the problem and solved it with the new version. Have fun again!

content: Its a great game and fun to play, but crashes on start up after the last update. Please fix - Nexus 6P
Things are too small to read and press.
The major issue I have with the game is that it crashes often, I have yet to play a full game.
Interface is too small, even on my 9 inch tablet.
Loved the board game but the UK is terrible. Icons are too small and placing tiles is way more exhausting than it should be.
Rules aren't accessible within the app, no key to colour code, thus no easy way to check how many points each building is worth
The UX is not suitable for mobilr
The app itself is terrible with nothing for instructions and a lame tutorial.  The game itself is uninspired and boring.

Alhambra is immensely fun, and this game obviously reflects that. However, the UI is very difficult. Nearly all elements are too small to accurately tap, even on large phablets. I'd pass unless you have a tablet

Technically the games great however as far as I'm concerned it's flat out broken. I can't place tiles so there are walls anywhere but the final perimeter of my alhambra. My a.i. opponents can. This guarantees that I lose! End of story. Otherwise a faithful interpretation of a great game, just pointless at the monment.
Thanks, great game. Procrastinated with it way too long now... Better go to bed.
You are not allowed to rotate tiles in Alhambra!!  People, please quit adding this to you list of gripes and improvements.
It's a blast, whether a 2(+) player game! And it doesn't take long to learn!
Terrible buggy ui. Non intuitive controls.
And didn't save the progress. Very disappointing. This has happened multiple times during a pass and play match when swapping a tile on the board with one from the reserve.

I have a feeling that it wasnt devices for an android device as the user interface isnt overly friendly. Often the images and details are too small making a good app almost unplayable. Hope this gets a fix!
How the hell do you move the market when it get slid under your money? Stupid programing mistake fix it do not allow the market to be slid anywhere!
Game is fine. Only thing that confuses me is the lack of ability to rotate tiles before placing them.
Alhambra

Ignore the reviews that say this app is buggy, it has been fixed. Ignore the reviews that say you cannot rotate the tiles, you are not meant to. Reasonably good digital version of the boardgame. Race of nations (Through the ages) is vastly better game with far better graphics and it is free! Try that instead.

From a very experienced board gamer I say : Great game that follows the board game's rules well. Very easy to play, stable but a challenge to win. Like most games it needs a polish of the online and save game. There is no reason NOT to buy this if you like games. BTW in the real game you can rotate tiles either!  That's half the challenge!

Buy the physical game instead of this one. I play Multi-player Pass and Play, it crashes.  I play solo and try to move something from reserve, it crashes.  Hopefully the real one won't crash when you play it.
Graphics aren't everything, but this game needs to be prettied up to compete against a lot of the other stellar looking board games on the Play Store.
One persons complaint is you cannot rotate tiles.  i dont know if you have played the board game, but you are not allowed to rotate tiles, so this rendition is totally accurate to the board game.
I was a little disappointed by the interface and random addition players.

Played on an 8" tablet. Text was readable.  Major gripe is being unable to rotate the tiles when placing in your Alhambra. Though the tile you want it available you cannot use it because it HAS to be placed in the same orientation as displayed in the market.

Font and graphics are too small, starting with the Settings screen, where the control options are so tiny that it took 10 minutes just to get the music control to respond to my fingers.  Still Can't get the View control to respond, which I assume might help with image size.  This is on a Note 4 phablet by the way...
Great game, wish there were more like it.
Dull
Exactly like the board game. Would love online multiplayer
Needs AI for pass-and-play! Besides that, great game.

Very enjoyable when it works for a complete game, which is only about 20% of the time.   The game crashes more often than not and as there is no save feature, your progress is lost.   Also, on large screen devices (Galaxy Note 3 here), the menus and buttons are tiny. Have to play with the stylus, which is ok but then the game crashes just as you're starting to enjoy it.
I am totally addicted :-), haven't found a bug yet, bought it about 3 weeks ago and play it everyday at least ! 5 to 8 times.
I really like it
Would give it 5 stars if they included the card that shows how many points you get at each scoring round and how many of each tile/building type exists.
It's mobile Alhambra, but crashes alot. Almost unplayable ;(
Alhambra is an excellent European-style board game. The ai is very tough to beat and will play the game tactically. The app itself crashes and has bugs so the rating is decreased to reflect this.
Doesn't work.

This is an enjoyable game and a good, albeit not a great looking, digital version. The annoyance is that you can't rotate tiles, so it's very hard to make a long wall. The many drawers and panels are a little confusing, and having the main buttons at the top of the screen mean that your hands are often blocking things while you tap the controls.  It could do with a UX overhaul, but apart from the lack of tile rotation it's a perfectly playable game.
No matter my selections, I cannot get the Register button to become available.  Tried to play solo, no dice.  Empty location with no buttons to start game.  I don't get it?  Refunded game.
Excellent game and app to match.
Nothing wrong with this game as far as I can tell. The interface could be a little more intuitive but I figure a few things out eventually. Keep up the great work.
OK its much much better now! Well done Queens ;)

I really enjoy the actual board game of this, and the app does allow me to play it however there are issues. The game does crash perhaps 15% of the time. It also feels very clunky and buggy. I also wish the game didn't auto rotate even when my screen rotate is switched off. If they bring this app up to a standard closer to fantasy flight's apps then I'd give it 5 stars but right now it doesn't feel like it is worth the price compared to other apps around.
I can't get more than two turns in without the game crashing.   Every time.   Needs to be fixed.

Shame that you cant turn the tiles to suit your needs like you can in real life.  A tile may be available that you could buy and use if you were playing for real but not on this because it's facing the wrong way and there is no option to rotate them.    Would go up to 4 stars if the above function were available. Loses star for small text!
Needs to be fixed, crashes when I switch apps long enough....say for example a phone call.
Excellent re-creation of the board game.

This version is true to the original, but buggy, lacks turn notification, doesn't let you exit games before they are competed, has an obtuse and instructionless online game establishing/joining system, hard to identify where to click/easy to make mistakes.
It bugs me this doesn't function well and unlike a lot of apps there's no refund option on poorly functioning games like this.

Needs an update. Does not feel like an app worth Its money. frequent crashes	There is no option to save your game or to resume play. I've had the game crash (update)more than a few times and when going back you had to start a new game. Does not feel like an app worth Its money.. free Apps work better
Fun game when it works. Crashes quite a bit. Asus tf700.

The game is a good representation of thr tabletop version, but the performace is terrible (slow), it crashes all the time and is buggy in game (you cant see your money cards as an example).  I wouldn't recommend this until it is updated.
There is a problem on my small screen phone where sometimes I can't quite make out the costs or scoring. However despite this I am completely hooked on the game!
Runs slow on both 1st gen Nexus 7 and Galaxy Nexus.  Crashing frequently on Galaxy Nexus.
Text is still a little too small but otherwise a great game. Looks good on a 10 and 7 inch screen. The new HD graphics look fantastic. I don't think I will even download it on my phone.
This game was better legible on my smartphone (Samsung Galaxy S1) than on a 7" tablet, which was totally unexpected. If the font size is improved, this game is great.
Great game.
Highly recommended for tablets. Some text is tiny (but just legible) even on  7" screen.
The text is very small on a phone, should perhaps warn the buyer that it is intended for tablets.  Some text errors as well with overlaps and such.
